im/her get an early start on building up damage. <br>
<br>
While there's doubtless some skilled people who have fun competing against each other in their respective groups, I think there's a lot more people learning incredibly bad raid habits early on with the current system. Most people start out raiding in situations where the raid really is overpowered relative to the place -- say multigroup raids in Kael arena. Instead of focusing on mana management, debuffing and aggro control it's a shooting gallery where the fastest and biggest guns win the prize.<br>
<br>
But I do agree that there'll be more problems (real or imagined) with casters on raids. It's a lot harder to tell if a wizard's effective than a meleer who actually has to stand up and haul ass over to a mob. Lucky that mages have Jobaner to show that we're at least conscious and pressing a button once during a fight.<br>
