I disagree here..<br>
<br>
Both wizards AND rogues can KS almost at will.  They both have massive DPS when they know how/what/when to let loose.<br>
<br>
Trying being a 3rd cleric group with druids, mages and enchanters.  You tell me when I might get Exp on raids.. I didn't think so.<br>
<br>
This &quot;shared exp&quot; is a VERY good idea if for no other reason than that it would help stop casters from over-nuking in attempts to KS, thus drawing agro away from the actual tanks.  (NOT getting into why tanks cant hold agro, it happens)<br>
<br>
I think the comment about the &quot;shared exp loss&quot; was referring simply to a raid wipe.  For groups that have no chance of getting exp, deaths plain and simple suck.<br>
<br>
Monks die ALOT on raids, but they also have a &quot;chance&quot; at exp.  Warrior MT's tend to die a couple times, but not very often, and have a &quot;chance&quot; at exp.  Clerics tend to die on raids, FEW have a &quot;chance&quot; at getting exp.<br>
<br>
All I am saying is that if you are worried about people slacking... log the battles and go back and parse out the damage.  Regardless, I can only see too much good coming out of this.<br>
